Here's the minimal program (targeting `net8.0`):

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase };
var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(new Person("Jane", 30), options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

**Output:**
```
{"name":"Jane","age":30}
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` on `JsonSerializerOptions` — it converts PascalCase properties (`Name`, `Age`) to camelCase (`name`, `age`) during serialization. The record declaration goes after the top-level statements.
